
[1]usurpation

   USURPA'TION, n. [supra.] The act of seizing or occupying and enjoying
   the property of another, without right; as the usurpation of a throne;
   the usurpation of the supreme power. Usurpation, in a peculiar sense,
   denotes the absolute ouster and dispossession of the patron of a
   church, by presenting a clerk to a vacant benefice, who is thereupon
   admitted and instituted.
